      An object to access and change fields representing the varias aspects of a MOB
      interface  Clan 
      interface  ClanGovernment
      A class defining the characteristics of a clan government, and its membership.
      interface  ClanPosition
      A class for the characteristics of a position within a clan government.
      interface  Climate
      A climate represents the entire weather pattern of an area It does most of the mundane things related to weather changes based on season, area, and other factors.
      interface  CMMsg
      The core of event handling in CoffeeMud, a CMMsg represents an event that occurs.
      interface  CoffeeShop
      A CoffeeShop is an object for storing the inventory of a shopkeeper, banker, auctionhouse, merchant, or other object that implements the ShopKeeper interface for the purpose of selling goods and services.
      interface  CoffeeTableRow
      A CoffeeTableRow object represents a period of sustained statistics gathering.
      interface  Faction
      A Faction is an arbitrary numeric range, where different mobs/players can be within that range, if they have the faction at all.
      interface  HttpClient
      A simple utility for making HTTP requests, which is implemented as a builder-type object.
      interface  JournalEntry 
      interface  Law
      The Law interface defines an object containing the various infractions that are recognized for a given LegalObject, the officials that enforce the infractions, some guidelines on their behavior, and information their processes of enforcement.
      interface  LegalWarrant
      A LegalWarrant is an important object in the triad of LegalBehavior and Law objects, as a part of the CoffeeMud legal system.
      interface  Manufacturer
      A class for holding information about the manufacturer of electronics.
      interface  PhyStats
      The PhyStats interface is a state object that holds some basic information about just about every Physical object in the game.
      interface  PlayerAccount
      An interface for a base player account.
      interface  PlayerStats
      Accessible from any PC mob object, PlayerStats are the repository for all manner of player specific mob values.
      interface  Poll
      A Poll object manages the data and processes for all of the public and private voting polls available through the CoffeeMud POLL CREATE POLL, LIST POLLS, etc..
      interface  Quest
      A quest object manages the details and text for a single descriptive script that is scheduled and, when directed, spawns, creates, watches, shuts down, and cleans up the various objects, subsidiary quests, and existing objects modifications related to this Quest.
      interface  RoomnumberSet
      A class for holding CoffeeMud-style room IDs of the form AreaName#[NUMBER], for instance, Midgaard#3001 This class is totally awesome because it stores them in an efficient way (holding room ids 5-10 not as 5,6,7,8,9,10, but as 5,10), but sorts them for quick reads.
      interface  ScriptingEngine
      The interface for the main CoffeeMud scripting engine, which implements a scripting engine descended from the old mud codebases of the 90's usually called MOBPROG.
      interface  Session
      A Session object is the key interface between the internet user and their player MOB.
      interface  Social
      Although at one time a simple public variable object, the Social became an environmental when it became import to be able to pass it as a tool of a message for various purposes.
      interface  Tattoo
      Tattoos are arbitrary markers or flags.
      interface  TimeClock
      This interface represents more than a "Time Zone", but a complete calendar, a complete lunar cycle, and schedule for days and nights.
